---

Trim and cut the @green beans{80} into thirds.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char and soften, ~{2-3%mins}.

Turn the heat down to medium, then stir in the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds} more.

Once the beans have softened, stir in the @water{240}(ml) and @chicken stock paste{10}(g). Bring to the boil.

When boiling, remove from the heat, stir in the @couscous{120}(g) and cover with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Leave to the side for ~{8-10%mins} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken thigh{260}(g) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks and pop into a #bowl{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with salt and pepper, then mix. Set the salsa aside.

Once the chicken is cooked, stir the @korma curry paste{50}(g), @mango chutney{40}(g), half the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75}(g) and the @water{50}(ml) into the pan.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%mins}.

When everything's ready, share the couscous and beans out between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon the glazed chicken over the top.

Finish with a dollop of the remaining yoghurt and spoonfuls of the tomato salsa.

Enjoy!